{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"mathvariant","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes/mathvariant","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"\n    <ol>\n        <li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element\">MathML Reference</a></strong>\n\n        \n            </li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/maction\">&lt;maction&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/math\">&lt;math&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/menclose\">&lt;menclose&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/merror\">&lt;merror&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mfenced\">&lt;mfenced&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mfrac\">&lt;mfrac&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mi\">&lt;mi&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mmultiscripts\">&lt;mmultiscripts&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mn\">&lt;mn&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mo\">&lt;mo&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mover\">&lt;mover&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mpadded\">&lt;mpadded&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mphantom\">&lt;mphantom&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mroot\">&lt;mroot&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mrow\">&lt;mrow&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/ms\">&lt;ms&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mspace\">&lt;mspace&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msqrt\">&lt;msqrt&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mstyle\">&lt;mstyle&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msub\">&lt;msub&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msubsup\">&lt;msubsup&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msup\">&lt;msup&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtable\">&lt;mtable&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtd\">&lt;mtd&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtext\">&lt;mtext&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtr\">&lt;mtr&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/munder\">&lt;munder&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/munderover\">&lt;munderover&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/semantics\">&lt;semantics&gt;</a></li>\n        \n\n        \n    </ol>\n","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <strong><code>mathvariant</code></strong> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes\">global attribute</a> attribute sets a logical class for textual elements, which is visually\n  distinguished by using special <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_Alphanumeric_Symbols\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Mathematical Alphanumeric Symbols</a>.\n  With the exception of <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mi\"><code>mi</code></a> elements with a single character,\n  which are by convention italic, no special classes are used by default.\n</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect1\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> When possible, directly use <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_Alphanumeric_Symbols\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Mathematical Alphanumeric Symbols</a> instead of an explicit <code>mathvariant</code> attribute.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>math</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- a normal \"A\" --&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mtext</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>A<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mtext</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- an italic \"A\" i.e. \"𝐴\" --&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mtext</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">mathvariant</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>italic<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>A<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mtext</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- an italic \"A\" i.e. \"𝐴\"\n     (automatic italicization for mi elements with one character) --&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mi</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>A<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mi</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- a normal \"A\" --&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mi</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">mathvariant</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>normal<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>A<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mi</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- a normal \"cos\" --&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mi</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>cos<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mi</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- a bold \"cos\" i.e. \"𝐜𝐨𝐬\" --&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mi</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">mathvariant</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>bold<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>cos<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mi</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- a double-struck \"A\" i.e. \"𝔸\" --&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mi</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">mathvariant</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>double-struck<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>A<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mi</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- a fraktur \"A\" i.e. \"𝔄\" --&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mi</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">mathvariant</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>fraktur<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>A<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mi</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- a looped \"ب\" i.e. \"𞺁\" --&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mi</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">mathvariant</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>looped<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>ب<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mi</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- a stretched \"ب\" i.e. \"𞹡\" --&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>mi</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">mathvariant</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>stretched<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>ب<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>mi</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>math</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"values","title":"Values","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>\n    <code>normal</code>\n    -: Use default rendering (no transformations applied).\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>bold</code>\n    -: Try and use bold characters e.g. \"𝐀\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>italic</code>\n    -: Try and use italic characters e.g. \"𝐴\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>bold-italic</code>\n    -: Try and use bold-italic characters e.g. \"𝑨\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>double-struck</code>\n    -: Try and use double-struck characters e.g. \"𝔸\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>bold-fraktur</code>\n    -: Try and use bold-fraktur characters e.g. \"𝕬\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>script</code>\n    -: Try and use script characters e.g. \"𝒜\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>bold-script</code>\n    -: Try and use bold-script characters e.g. \"𝓐\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>fraktur</code>\n    -: Try and use fraktur characters e.g. \"𝔄\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>sans-serif</code>\n    -: Try and use sans-serif characters e.g. \"𝖠\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>bold-sans-serif</code>\n    -: Try and use bold-sans-serif characters e.g. \"𝗔\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>sans-serif-italic</code>\n    -: Try and use sans-serif-italic characters e.g. \"𝘈\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>sans-serif-bold-italic</code>\n    -: Try and use sans-serif-bold-italic characters e.g. \"𝘼\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>monospace</code>\n    -: Try and use monospace characters e.g. \"𝙰\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>initial</code>\n    -: Try and use initial characters e.g. \"𞸢\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>tailed</code>\n    -: Try and use tailed characters e.g. \"𞹂\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>looped</code>\n    -: Try and use looped characters e.g. \"𞺂\".\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <code>stretched</code>\n    -: Try and use stretched characters e.g. \"𞹢\".\n  </li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"notes_on_mathml_versions","title":"Notes on MathML versions","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><code>mathvariant</code> values other than <code>normal</code> were designed for backward compatibility. Authors are encouraged to instead directly use the corresponding Unicode characters from the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_Alphanumeric_Symbols\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Mathematical Alphanumeric Symbols</a>.</li>\n  <li>MathML Core relies on <code>text-transform</code> to implement the <code>mathvariant</code> attribute, but implementations of older MathML versions may follow a different approach to implement similar behavior.</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"query":"mathml.global_attributes.mathvariant","specifications":[]}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"data":null,"query":"mathml.global_attributes.mathvariant","browsers":null}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  </p>\n  On Firefox, some <code>mathvariant</code> values are only implemented starting with Firefox 28 and require appropriate <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Fonts\">math fonts</a>.\n<p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>All <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes\">global attributes</a>.</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/text-transform\"><code>text-transform</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Notes on MathML versions","id":"notes_on_mathml_versions"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The mathvariant global attribute attribute sets a logical class for textual elements, which is visually\n  distinguished by using special Mathematical Alphanumeric Symbols.\n  With the exception of mi elements with a single character,\n  which are by convention italic, no special classes are used by default.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-09T04:10:27.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/mathml/global_attributes/mathvariant","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/mathml/global_attributes/mathvariant/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/2039591f80b7218cbc4f5918f2a873814e83321c","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML","title":"MathML"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes","title":"Global attributes"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes/mathvariant","title":"mathvariant"}],"pageTitle":"mathvariant - MathML | MDN","noIndexing":false}}